The Social Insurance Institute of Mexico runs a research project to detect the gene for obesity in children and adolescents supported by IPN specialists.
The Instituto Mexicano del Seguro Social - IMSS (Mexican Social Insurance Institute) announced that it will lead a research project to discover the gene for obesity in children and adolescents under the title "Genetic obesity in childhood and youth," to find genetic markers in conjunction with overweight.
Miguel Cruz López, head of the Unidad de Investigación Médica en Bioquímica (Department of Medical Research, Priority Biochemistry) at the Hospital de Especialidades del Centro Médico Nacional Siglo XXI said that an interdisciplinary team consisting of doctors, nurses, food specialists and social workers was built.
