When the target of 500 to 600 investigators has been reached, the study will be continued at Independencia Sports Square (in the south of the capital district) and completed by Morelos (in the north of the capital district).
He stated that the aim of the study was to learn the factors and the role of genetics in connection with the development of obesity and the identification of risk factors for Mexican children and adolescents to prevent chronic degenerative diseases.
