He stated that an average of 65 percent of Mexican (in) was Indian-American, 30 percent of European and 5 percent of African descendants, reflecting the genes associated with diabetes and overweight.
In general, he declared that the genetics of obesity pressed in the inability to burn the surplus of the energy taken to us (calories), so that it was stored in the form of fat.
